<h2>3. Gmail Setup Instructions</h2>

<div class="step-box">
<h3>Step 1: Open Gmail Settings</h3>
<ol>
  <li>Open Gmail in your web browser</li>
  <li>Click the <strong>gear icon</strong> (⚙️) in the top right</li>
  <li>Click <strong>"See all settings"</strong></li>
</ol>
</div>

<div class="step-box">
<h3>Step 2: Navigate to Signature Section</h3>
<ol>
  <li>Stay on the <strong>"General"</strong> tab</li>
  <li>Scroll down to find <strong>"Signature"</strong> section</li>
  <li>Click <strong>"+ Create new"</strong></li>
  <li>Name your signature (e.g., "PLM Professional")</li>
</ol>
</div>

<div class="step-box">
<h3>Step 3: Add Your Signature</h3>
<ol>
  <li>Open the HTML signature file in a web browser</li>
  <li>Select all content (Ctrl+A or Cmd+A)</li>
  <li>Copy (Ctrl+C or Cmd+C)</li>
  <li>Paste into Gmail signature editor (Ctrl+V or Cmd+V)</li>
</ol>
</div>

<div class="step-box">
<h3>Step 4: Set as Default</h3>
<ol>
  <li>Under "Signature defaults" choose your new signature</li>
  <li>Set for both "New emails" and "On reply/forward"</li>
  <li>Scroll to bottom and click <strong>"Save Changes"</strong></li>
</ol>
</div>

<div class="warning">
<strong>Note:</strong> Gmail may strip some formatting. For best results, use the image-based signature created in Canva.
</div>

<hr>

<h2>4. Outlook Setup Instructions</h2>

<h3>Outlook Desktop (Windows)</h3>

<div class="step-box">
<ol>
  <li>Open Outlook</li>
  <li>Click <strong>File</strong> → <strong>Options</strong></li>
  <li>Click <strong>Mail</strong> in the left sidebar</li>
  <li>Click the <strong>"Signatures..."</strong> button</li>
  <li>Click <strong>"New"</strong> to create a new signature</li>
  <li>Name it "PLM Signature"</li>
  <li>Open the HTML file in a browser, copy the content</li>
  <li>Paste into the signature editor</li>
  <li>Click <strong>OK</strong> to save</li>
</ol>
</div>

<h3>Outlook Web (Office 365)</h3>

<div class="step-box">
<ol>
  <li>Click the <strong>gear icon</strong> (⚙️) in the top right</li>
  <li>Click <strong>"View all Outlook settings"</strong></li>
  <li>Go to <strong>Mail</strong> → <strong>Compose and reply</strong></li>
  <li>Under "Email signature", paste your signature content</li>
  <li>Check "Automatically include my signature on new messages"</li>
  <li>Click <strong>"Save"</strong></li>
</ol>
</div>

<hr>

<h2>5. Apple Mail Setup Instructions</h2>

<div class="step-box">
<h3>macOS</h3>
<ol>
  <li>Open <strong>Mail</strong> app</li>
  <li>Click <strong>Mail</strong> → <strong>Preferences</strong> (or Cmd+,)</li>
  <li>Click the <strong>"Signatures"</strong> tab</li>
  <li>Select your email account on the left</li>
  <li>Click the <strong>"+"</strong> button to add new signature</li>
  <li>Name it "PLM Signature"</li>
  <li>Uncheck "Always match my default message font"</li>
  <li>Open HTML file in Safari, copy content, paste into signature box</li>
  <li>Close preferences to save</li>
</ol>
</div>

<div class="step-box">
<h3>iOS (iPhone/iPad)</h3>
<ol>
  <li>Open <strong>Settings</strong></li>
  <li>Scroll down and tap <strong>Mail</strong></li>
  <li>Tap <strong>Signature</strong></li>
  <li>Enter your signature text (HTML not fully supported)</li>
  <li>For best results on iOS, use a simple text version or image</li>
</ol>
</div>

